events.name: New York Knicks at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points, Evan Mobley added 21 and the Cleveland Cavaliers bullied the New York Knicks from the start Friday night, winning 142-105 in a matchup of two of the Eastern Conference's top teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell and Evan Mobley power East-leading Cavaliers to 142-105 blowout of Knicks

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 10 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter and Jaren Jackson Jr. blocked a driving floater by Orlando’s Paolo Banchero in the final second to give the Memphis Grizzlies a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant's 4th-quarter burst, Jackson's last-second block give Grizzlies 105-104 win over Magic

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 19 points in his return to Washington, and the Milwaukee Bucks overcame Giannis Antetokounmpo's foul trouble to beat the Wizards 104-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks overcome Antetokounmpo's foul trouble and hold on for a 104-101 victory over Wizards

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 10 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter and overtime, Andrew Wiggins added 25 points and the Miami Heat snapped a four-game skid by beating the Toronto Raptors 120-111 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 28 points as Heat beat Raptors 120-111 in overtime to snap 4-game skid

events.name: Detroit Pistons at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 25 points and 12 assists and keyed a 19-0 run as the Detroit Pistons won their fifth straight game, 125-110 over the San Antonio Spurs on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham has 25 points and 12 assists and Pistons use big run to beat Spurs 125-110

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 35 points, P.J. Washington Jr. had 20 of his 24 points in the first half and the Dallas Mavericks beat the New Orleans Pelicans 111-103 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 35 points to help the Mavericks beat the Pelicans 111-103 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 35 points, Alperen Sengun added 24 points and 13 rebounds and the Houston Rockets defeated the Minnesota Timberwolves 121-115 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 35 points to lead Rockets past Timberwolves 121-115

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 21 points and the West-leading Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Utah Jazz 130-107 on Friday night for their eighth victory in nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: West-leading Thunder beat the Jazz 130-107 for 8th victory in 9 games

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield and Moses Moody had 22 points each and the Golden State Warriors beat the Sacramento Kings 132-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield, Moody lead Warriors with 22 points each in 132-106 blowout over Kings
